<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-03-15</DATELINE><TITLE>Virucidal Activity of World Health Organizationâ€“Recommended Formulations Against Enveloped Viruses, Including Zika, Ebola, and Emerging Coronaviruses</TITLE><BODY>The World Health Organization (WHO) published 2 alcohol-based formulations to be used in healthcare settings and for outbreak-associated infections, but inactivation efficacies of these products have not been determined against (re-)emerging viruses. In this study, we evaluated the virucidal activity of these WHO products in a comparative analysis. Zika virus (ZIKV), Ebola virus (EBOV), severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus (SARS-CoV), and Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) as (re-)emerging viral pathogens and other enveloped viruses could be efficiently inactivated by both WHO formulations, implicating their use in healthcare systems and viral outbreak situations.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>